history.content:
As stated on the Enrollment FAQ, in order to find out if a lab is has space, you have to add the enrollments from EECS 106A, BioE 106A, and EECS 206A together to see how many people have enrolled. All of the labs are full. I know it's not an ideal system, but we don't have control over it.

There are currently 21 people on the waitlist (from both the undergrad and graduate sections. So you do have a slim chance of getting in, but I'd find a backup class.

I selected an open lab and discussion when enrolling for BIOE C106A, but I was still put on the waitlist anyway. At this point, I am 5th on the waitlist, and there are 12 total people in this part of the class. I am not sure whether I can get it from the waitlist alone. Will the class expand, or should I drop the class?
history.subject: EECS/BIOE C106A Waitlist
